nodes.text: F-29-PSKx, also known simply as F-29, was a masculine F series repair droid with blue photoreceptors and silver plating, with a blue trim. By the year 4.3 ABY, he worked for the Star Tours travel agency. While visiting its Tomorrowland Starport, F-29 felt homesick and often called his girlfriend using a Star*Link booth.

F-29-PSKx was created for Tokyo Disneyland's simulator ride theme park attraction Star Tours, which opened on July 12, 1989. He, alongside F-25-OJSx, were the only F series droids in the ride to not be identified by name on the "Spot the Droid" posters or in Complete Guide to Star Tours, being instead only identified as "Passenger Droid" and "Spacecap Droid," respectively.
